\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>"No matter how much I do, the work never ends... What's
that? Working on a holiday?"

\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>"To survive, I just have to accept it... I'm not even
expecting any extra pay."

\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>Hm...? That's a name I haven't heard in a while. If I
remember correctly, she suddenly quit last year.

\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>She had an unusual optimism for one of our employees, and
she knew a lot of people. That's why everyone was so
disappointed when she left.

\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>According to the rumors, she didn't get along with the
executives... She was even helping out other teams' succubi.

\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>Knowing her, there must have been a reason, but as you can
see, we're too swamped to pay much attention. I wonder how
she's doing now...

\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>Maybe that person who's always at the counter knows
something? She seems to be on good terms with the
executives, after all.
\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>Hey there. Tough working on the weekend, huh?

\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>None of the seniors came in today... *sigh* Sorry, but could
you give me a hand?
Yes
No

\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>Thank you. Here's the to-do list. If there's anything you
don't understand, just ask.
\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>Good work today. Be careful on your way home.

\nc<Lewd Demon Employee>Me? I'll go home after I finish cleaning up... *sigh* What
time is the last bus again...
